State Capture Inquiry chairperson Raymond Zondo has something to get off chest this morning. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - State capture inquiry chairperson Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo said a witness -- whose identity is being protected -- is going to testify on 20 and 21 September. Zondo said Wednesday's proceedings have adjourned but will continue on Thursday with a new witness. The former head of the Agriculture Department, Peter Thabethe, is expected to testify. READ: Plans to fund Estina dairy farm fast-tracked, says witness On Tuesday, the controversial Estina dairy farm was in the spotlight at the inquiry. Zondo heard how plans to fund the infamous Estina Dairy Project were fast-tracked at a staggering rate. Small-scale farmers were the intended beneficiaries of Vrede-based project but they never saw any of the money. The inquiry into state capture has been postponed to Thursday.